1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:03,450
Imagine writing in Go but getting C-level performance!

2
00:00:03,450 --> 00:00:08,975
That's the promise of Solod, a new subset of Go that translates directly to C code.

3
00:00:08,975 --> 00:00:17,650
This project aims to bring the simplicity of Go to areas traditionally dominated by C, like embedded systems or operating system kernels.

4
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:24,712
It's a fascinating bridge between two powerful programming paradigms, offering developers the best of both worlds.

